  "title": "ISic001151. Funerary inscription for Opetreia Letois",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Alex Antoniou</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ὀπετρηία Λητώι Μου\n                    σαίου γυνήι\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ὀπετρηία\"><span data-text=\"Ὀπετρηία\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Ὀπετρηία\">Ὀπετρηία</span></span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Λητώι\"><span data-text=\"Λητώι\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"Λητώ\">Λητώι</span></span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μου\n                    σαίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"gamonym\" data-text=\"Μου\n                    σαίου\"><span data-text=\"Μου\n                    σαίου\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Μουσαῖος\">Μου-<br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>σαίου</span></span></span>  <span data-text=\"γυνήι\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"γυνή\">γυνήι</span></span>  <span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρε</span>  <span data-text=\"χρησ\n                    τὴ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">χρησ-<br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>τὴ</span>  <span data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"καί\">καὶ</span>  <span data-text=\"εὐσεβής\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"εὐσεβής\">εὐσεβής</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive-simple-lemmatized\">  <div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <span data-text=\"Ὀπετρηία\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Ὀπετρηία\">Ὀπετρηία</span>  <span data-text=\"Λητώι\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"Λητώ\">Λητώι</span>  <span data-text=\"Μουσαίου\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Μουσαῖος\">Μουσαίου</span>  <span data-text=\"γυνήι\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"γυνή\">γυνήι</span>  <span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρε</span>  <span data-text=\"χρηστὴ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">χρηστὴ</span>  <span data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"καί\">καὶ</span>  <span data-text=\"εὐσεβής\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"εὐσεβής\">εὐσεβής</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Alex Antoniou</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ὀπετρηία Λητώι Μου\n                    σαίου γυνήι\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ὀπετρηία\"><span data-text=\"Ὀπετρηία\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Ὀπετρηία\">ΟΠΕΤΡΗΙΑ</span></span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Λητώι\"><span data-text=\"Λητώι\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"Λητώ\">ΛΗΤΩΙ</span></span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μου\n                    σαίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"gamonym\" data-text=\"Μου\n                    σαίου\"><span data-text=\"Μου\n                    σαίου\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Μουσαῖος\">ΜΟΥ<br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>ΣΑΙΟΥ</span></span></span><span data-text=\"γυνήι\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"γυνή\">ΓΥΝΗΙ</span></span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span><span data-text=\"χρησ\n                    τὴ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">ΧΡΗΣ<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>ΤΗ</span><span data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"καί\">ΚΑΙ</span><span data-text=\"εὐσεβής\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"εὐσεβής\">ΕΥΣΕΒΗΣ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"Ὀπετρηία\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Ὀπετρηία\">ΟΠΕΤΡΗΙΑ</span><span data-text=\"Λητώι\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"Λητώ\">ΛΗΤΩΙ</span><span data-text=\"Μουσαίου\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Μουσαῖος\">ΜΟΥΣΑΙΟΥ</span><span data-text=\"γυνήι\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"γυνή\">ΓΥΝΗΙ</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span><span data-text=\"χρηστὴ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">ΧΡΗΣΤΗ</span><span data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"καί\">ΚΑΙ</span><span data-text=\"εὐσεβής\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"εὐσεβής\">ΕΥΣΕΒΗΣ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001151_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo civico di Termini Imerese\" src=\"ISic001151_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001151.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo civico di Termini Imerese\" src=\"ISic001151-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text from autopsy</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou</a></p>  <p>Opetreia Letois, wife of Mousaios, worthy and pious, farewell.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The opening of the inscription is disputed. Kaibel (IG) assumes the omega opening line 1 is an error of the stonecutter, for theta, whereas Brugnone believes Opetreia is a transcription of the Latin nomen, the feminine form of Opetreius, both of which are attested epigraphically (outside of Sicily). In relation to Letois (here in the vocative), Brugnone believes the deceased to have been a freedwoman who adopted the nomen of the person who had freed her. The name Mousaios is common, although not necessarily in Sicily.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li></li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">332</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a>  </li><li> Brugnone 1974 13 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001397\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001397</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Letters are fairly regularly spaced in lines 1-2, but become more irregular in line 3. Letters have light serifs. Letter forms irregular and inconsistent. Two forms of alpha are used: in line one, alpha has an oblique mid-bar which slopes to the right, in lines 2-3, alpha has a broken mid-bar. Omega in line 1 is flat and broad. Beta in line 3 is extremely flat and pointed, and is potentially a correction from a Rho.</p> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Β-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Β type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Β-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Β type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Η-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Η type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ι-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ι type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Λ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Λ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-tyoe3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ tyoe3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Χ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Χ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type1.4.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type1.4</a> </p> Line 1  25-26  Line 2  20-26  Line 3  23-28  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
